           <p>Welcome to the Menu Bar!</p>
          
          <p>In this tutorial we will be going more into detail about what the Menu Bar is, what are the different
          menus, and some of the stuff they have inside of them. We will not being going deeply into every single item
          because there is a lot of them and it can get tedious.</p>
          
          <p>The Menu Bar is essentially a bar that holds a bunch of menus. That's why it is called a Menu Bar. Each menu 
          is very specific and inside each menu, it has items that does very specific things. 
          
          <p>For example, think of the Menu Bar as your dresser. Each drawer has specific items in them. Let's say 
          your top drawer has your t-shirts and the drawer below that has your pants. You are not going to 
          find a t-shirt inside of your pants drawer. You are going to find your shirt in the t-shirts drawer. 
          Your t-shirt drawer might have tank tops, shirts with buttons, and shirts with strips. It might have
          different kind of shirts, but in the end it has items that go with that theme.</p>
          
          <p>Same thing with the Menu Bar and the menus. Each menu follows a theme so that way we can know where to go
          when we need something.</p>
          
          
          <p></p>In the Menu Bar, the names of our menus are:</p>
          <p><li>File</li>
          <li>Edit</li>
          <li>Assets</li>
          <li>GameObject</li>
          <li>Component</li>
          <li>GoogleVR</li>
         <li>Window</li>
          <li>Help</li></p>
          
          <p>Don't worry if you don't one of these menus in your bar. Actually it's a good thing if you don't. 
          Some of these menus will be added on in Tutorial 3, as we start to build our game.</p> 
          
          <p>In the File menu, we have everything that has to go with saving your project. Here is where
          you will go to save, create, and export your project. If you want to make a new project, you
          can go here to do it. Do you want to take a copy of your game and see it on your phone? We will
          do it through this menu.</p>
          
          <p>In the Edit menu, we have everything that has to do with making changes to your project. Did
          you realize you just made a mistake? You can undo it here. Do you want to copy and then paste something?
          This is where you will go to do it.</p>
          
          <p>The Assets menu is the menu where you can go to add assets to your project. Assets are premade objects
            that someone else made that we can use. Whenever you get a new asset, you can see it in the 
            Project folder at the bottom of the screen.</p>
          
          <p>The GameObject menu is where we can go to make a new object that we can add to our game.
          This is also the place where we can create lights, sounds, and a bunch of different items.</p>
          
          <p>The Component menu is where you can add meshes, physics, and other items to your game objects.
          Meshes are how your game object looks like. Physics include things like adding gravity.</p>
          <p>While we will eventually see the GoogleVR menu, we are not going to directly interact with it. 
          Essentially, this is the menu to go to when you want to report something wrong with GoogleVR or
          look at all of the information behind it.</p>
          <p>The Window menu is a menu that allows you to change and mess with the way the Unity screen looks
          on your computer. If you ever exit out of the Game Scene or move things around, you can go here
          to get everything reset to default, or how it originally looked like when you opened your project. </p>
          <p>In the Help menu, you can go here to check out your version of Unity, go to the Unity forum and ask
          for help, and check for updates. </p>
          
          
           
         <p> Listed below, I have details about some of the items in these menus that we will be using a lot in future
          tutorials. </p>
          
          <p> Don't worry if later on you don't remeber what something does
          or the shortcuts! Every tutorial in the the game making tutorials
          will have a link back to this section or to <p><b><a href="help2">Tutorial 2 Help</a>.</b></p></p>
          
        
